<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="63" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[62,1726,2201,2644]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
Oguma separated the Formosan form as a distinct subspecies from the 
<typeStatus box="[1539,1613,2384,2422]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">type</typeStatus>
form mainly by the smaller body-size. Until a more comprehensive investigation would be made I treat it as 
<emphasis box="[426,614,2494,2532]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Selys" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[426,609,2494,2532]" class="Insecta" family="Libellulidae" genus="Deielia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phaon">D. phaon</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[62,1726,2201,2644]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
The 
<typeStatus box="[239,392,2549,2587]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oguma" authorityYear="1915" box="[466,687,2549,2587]" class="Insecta" family="Cordulegastridae" genus="Chlorogomphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevistigma">
<emphasis box="[466,687,2549,2587]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">brevistigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are represented by three males and one heterochromatic female: the male bearing the label “Shirin, 
<date box="[903,1056,2603,2641]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">31. VII.</date>
” is selected as 
<typeStatus box="[1370,1532,2603,2641]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
